dcterms:creator: Damien LaRocque
William Guimont-Martin
David-Alexandre Duclos
Philippe Giguère
François Pomerleau
dcterms:description: BorealTC is a publicly available dataset for proprioceptive-based terrain classification, recorded with a Husky A200. It contains 116 minutes of IMU, motor current, and wheel odometry data, focusing on typical boreal forest terrains, notably snow, ice, and silty loam.
dcterms:title: BorealTC

dcterms:creator: F. Vulpi
A. Milella
R. Marani
G. Reina
dcterms:description: The Vulpi dataset is used for deep terrain classification by autonomous robots, containing data collected with a Clearpath Robotics Husky. It includes various terrain types and is referenced for its accuracy in terrain classification tasks.
dcterms:title: Vulpi Dataset

dcterms:creator: J. Zurn
W. Burgard
A. Valada
dcterms:description: The Freiburg Terrains dataset is utilized for self-supervised visual terrain classification from unsupervised acoustic feature learning, providing a basis for evaluating terrain classification methods.
dcterms:title: Freiburg Terrains

dcterms:creator: J. Zurn
W. Burgard
A. Valada
dcterms:description: The Jackal Robot 7-Class Terrain Datasets are used for self-supervised visual terrain classification, providing a comprehensive evaluation of terrain classification methods.
dcterms:title: Jackal Robot 7-Class Terrain Datasets

dcterms:creator: P. Dallaire
K. Walas
P. Giguere
B. Chaib-draa
dcterms:description: The Messor Walking Machine Data is used for learning terrain types with the Pitman-Yor process mixtures of Gaussians for a legged robot, contributing to the understanding of terrain classification.
dcterms:title: Messor Walking Machine Data

dcterms:creator: M. Bednarek
M. R. Nowicki
K. Walas
dcterms:description: The ANYmal Walking Robot Data is utilized for improved haptic transformer for legged terrain classification, enhancing the understanding of terrain interaction.
dcterms:title: ANYmal Walking Robot Data

dcterms:creator: C. Allred
H. Kocabas
M. Harper
J. Pusey
dcterms:description: The Spot Robot Data is used for terrain-dependent power estimation for legged robots in unstructured environments, providing insights into terrain interaction.
dcterms:title: Spot Robot Data
